> Seems Spark handles it in the analysis phase

@pan3793, thanks for checking!

> The backward compatibility only affects adding columns or creating new tables. The settings spark.sql.iceberg.handle-timestamp-without-timezone and spark.sql.iceberg.use-timestamp-without-timezone-in-new-tables would convert a timestamp with timezone to a timestamp without a timezone. I'm leaning toward dropping this in 3.4.

@Fokko, I'd be inclined to rely on `spark.sql.timestampType` instead of these two properties. Otherwise, it would be weird to have an alternative solution that overrides the Spark behavior. It only existed as a workaround.

@Fokko, how do you feel about adding the implementation while ignoring failing vectorized tests for now? I think we will need to add tests for places that convert filters and implement `InternalRow`, like pointed above by @takeono.
